body:
Not having proxied uploads complicates things even more in case of a slightly more complex setup.

Let's say that you're deploying a service on AWS ECS/ECR and set up the necessary infra (S3 bucket and access policies) through Terraform scripts. The mlflow service is given access to the bucket, and the end user assumes that you just push stuff to the service and it will get sorted out on that end; 

But with the current implementation, you have to create your individual IAM role, log in to AWS with that role and change the terraform to give that role access to the bucket in addition to the service... Times the number of clients? Not a really sustainable approach as others have noted above.
